#There are -99s in the data that needs to be recoded

recoded_green <-
  green_data %>%
  na_if(-99) %>%
  mutate(
    student = recode(student, "1" = "nonstudent", "2" = "student"))
  1. Compute total scores for the four scales. Recode variables as needed.
reversed <- dictionary %>%
  filter(
    Keying == -1 | Keying == -2) %>%
  pull(Item)

reversed
##  [1] "green2"  "comp6"   "comp7"   "comp8"   "comp9"   "comp10"  "intel7" 
##  [8] "intel8"  "intel9"  "intel10" "open7"   "open8"   "open9"   "open10"
reversed_green <-recoded_green %>%
  mutate(
    across(
      all_of(reversed),
           ~ recode(.x, 
                    "5" = 1, 
                    "4" = 2, 
                    "3" = 3, 
                    "2" = 4, 
                    "1" = 5)))
View(reversed_green)

total_green <-
  reversed_green %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(green_tot = mean(c_across(green1:green5)),
         comp_tot = mean(c_across(comp1:comp10)),
         intel_tot = mean(c_across(intel1:intel10)),
         open_tot = mean(c_across(open1:open10))) %>% 
  na.omit() %>%
  select(id, student, green_tot, comp_tot, intel_tot, open_tot)

View(total_green)

  1. Rescale the variables so that they go from 0-100 instead of the original range. Name the rescaled variables *_pomp.
rescaled_green <-
  total_green %>%
  mutate(
    green_pomp = rescale(green_tot, 
                         to=c(0,100), 
                         from=c(1,5)),
    comp_pomp = rescale(comp_tot, 
                        to=c(0,100), 
                        from=c(1,5)),
    intel_pomp = rescale(intel_tot, 
                         to=c(0,100), 
                         from=c(1,5)),
    open_pomp = rescale(open_tot, 
                        to=c(0,100), 
                        from=c(1,5))) %>%
  select(id, 
         student, 
         green_pomp, 
         comp_pomp, 
         intel_pomp, 
         open_pomp)

View(rescaled_green)

#Non-students have a higher count on the green reputation scale than the students. 
#Non-students have a slightly wider distribution on the green reputation scale.
  1. Compute a summary table of means, SDs, medians, minima, and maxima for the four total scores for students and non-students.
rescaled_green %>%
  select(student, green_pomp, 
         comp_pomp, 
         intel_pomp, 
         open_pomp) %>%
  group_by(student) %>%
  summarize(
    across(c(green_pomp, 
             comp_pomp, 
             intel_pomp, 
             open_pomp),
           list(mean = ~mean(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
                sd = ~sd(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
                med = ~median(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
                min = ~min(.x, na.rm = TRUE),
                max = ~max(.x, na.rm = TRUE))))
